# Documentation Sync

When you modify code in `src/`, `config/`, or `scripts/`, **always** update the relevant docs:

| Changed | Update |
|---------|--------|
| Pipeline phases, data flow, component wiring | `docs/architecture.md` |
| Phase steps, CLI options, processing details | `docs/pipeline.md` |
| Model swap, new model, config change for a model | `docs/models.md` |
| Output JSON fields, new event types, coordinate systems | `docs/data_format.md` |
| Training data format, fine-tuning instructions, tuning params | `docs/training.md` |
| Evaluation metrics, GT format, evaluate.py options | `docs/evaluation.md` |
| Config keys added/removed/renamed | `config/default.yaml` comments + relevant docs |

Do not skip documentation updates — treat them as part of the same change.
